Bxc3 9. bxc3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Qc7 11. Ba2 {This is the third most popular line.} e5 
12. h3 Bf5 {A natuaral developing move.} 13. d5 Rad8 14. c4 e4 15. Nh4 Bc8 {At 
first it seems as if Black is under a bit of pressure. However, notice that both 
of White's bishops are awkwardly placed.} *

