1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. Nf3 c5 6. dxc5 Na6 7. a3 {An 
alternative to g3, but Black scores excellently in the resulting positions.} 
Bxc3+ 8. Qxc3 Nxc5 {Black will fianchetto his light squared bishop with a good 
position. If White every plays b4, hitting the knight, Black can play Nce4. 
White cannot kick it away with f3 because his knight is on f3.} *

