1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 b6 7. Bg5 Bb7 8. f3 
{This is White's more aggressive option.} h6 9. Bh4 {White has no interest in 
giving up the bishop pair.} d5 10. e3 {If White takes on d5 instead, Black 
should recapture with the pawn. This gives him a comfortable position because he 
is ahead in development and has nice central control.} Nbd7 11. cxd5 Nxd5 {Black 
is willing to trade queens.} 12. Bxd8 Nxc3 13. Bh4 Nd5 14. Bf2 c5 {White has the 
bishop pair, but Black has a very solid pawn structure.} *

