1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. Nf3 {This is a natural alternative 
to the main line with a3.} c5 {Black attacks White's center.} 6. dxc5 {If White 
chooses the move e3 instead, Black can calmly play d5.} Na6 7. g3 Nxc5 8. Bg2 
Nce4 9. O-O Nxc3 10. bxc3 {Black manages to double White's c-pawns on the 
semi-open file.} Be7 11. e4 {White's compensation is his central control.} d6 
12. e5 dxe5 13. Nxe5 Qc7 {Black has really good chances, especially considering 
White's ruined pawn structure on the queenside.} *

