[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "nimzo-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2359, variation/78838"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. Bg5 Bb7 6. Nd2 {White's idea is to 
prepare an e4 advance.} h6 7. Bh4 c5 {Black strikes in the center.} 8. d5 Bxc3 
{Black's dark-squared bishop is not actively helping in the fight for the 
center, so it is best to trade it off for White's knight on c3.} 9. bxc3 d6 
{Black prepares e5, closing the position.} 10. e4 e5 {Resulting positions remain 
closed and Black has very little to worry about.} *

