1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. Bg5 Bb7 6. Nd2 h6 7. Bh4 c5 8. a3 
{This is a sideline that White can try.} Bxc3 9. bxc3 d6 10. f3 Nc6 {Black is 
doing very well. His plan is to castle queenside and push his pawns on the 
kingside (starting with g5 hitting the bishop), going straight for White's 
king.} *

