1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. Bg5 Bb7 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 g5 8. Bg3 Ne4 
9. Qc2 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 d6 11. Bd3 f5 12. d5 Nd7 13. Nd4 {This is White's main 
alternative to taking on e4.} Ndc5 {White can continue by simply improving the 
position of his knight and adds support to the e6 pawn. After Qf6 and castling, 
Black has at least equality.} *

