1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. e3 {A solid alternative to the more 
common Bg5.} Bb7 6. Bd3 Ne4 7. O-O {Qc2 is an alternative move order after f5 
and O-O.} f5 {This is Black's more aggressive approach, which I enjoy playing.} 
8. Qc2 Bxc3 9. bxc3 O-O 10. Nd2 Qh4 11. f3 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 d6 {Black has a good 
position.} *

