1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. f3 {This is Black's most ambitious try against 
the Nimzo.} d5 {Black tries to break up the center. If you are a very aggressive 
player, I would recommend the move c5 instead. I prefer the principled move d5 
however, so c5 is not covered in this repertoire.} 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 {Black 
actually has a lead in development in this postion.} 7. cxd5 Nxd5 {Black's 
position is very solid. The same positon is reached in the main line of the 
Sämisch Variation.} 8. dxc5 Qa5 9. e4 Nf6 10. Be3 O-O *

