[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "nimzo-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2359, variation/78829"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. f3 d5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. 
Qd3 {This move is the much less popular alternative to dxc5.} b6 9. e4 Ba6 
{Black develops with tempo.} 10. Qd2 Bxf1 11. Kxf1 Ne7 {Black is left with a 
very nice position. Black's plan is to prove that White's pawn center is a 
weakness rather than an asset by putting pressure on it with his knights and 
rooks. Notice that White has not developed any of his pieces.} *

