[SourceTitle "06 Sämisch Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "nimzo-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2359, variation/78810"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 c5 6. f3 {This is White's 
second choice.} d5 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. dxc5 {This pawn structure is quite common in 
the Sämisch Variation. Black aims to exploit White's pawn weaknesses while 
White aims for central control with e4.} Qa5 9. e4 Nf6 {If Black takes on c3 
with his knight, White has an excellent position after the simple Qd2. Qxc3 wins 
back the pawn, but White has a clear advantage due to his suddenly active bishop 
after Bd2. Black does not lose a piece because of Qe5.} 10. Be3 O-O {Black has a 
good position.} *

[Event "Nimzo-Indian Defense- Tournament Edition"]
[Site "Sämisch Variation"]
