[SourceTitle "06 Sämisch Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "nimzo-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2359, variation/120839"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 {White immediately attack Black's bishop.} 
Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 {Black doubles White's pawns.} c5 {White's c4-pawn is weak, so 
Black stops it from moving any further down the board. Black's plan from here on 
focuses on attacking the weak pawn on c4.} 6. e3 {This is the main line. Black 
focuses on the weak c4 pawn while White tries to build up his center.} O-O 7. 
Bd3 Nc6 8. Ne2 b6 9. e4 Ne8 10. O-O Ba6 11. f4 f5 *

