[SourceTitle "08 Spielmann Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "nimzo-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2359, variation/78789"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qb3 {This is known as the Spielmann Variation. 
It is a minor variation and you will not see it very often when playing the 
Nimzo Indian.} c5 {Black protects the bishop and hits White's center.} 5. dxc5 
{This is the most popular move. White can also try Nf3.} Nc6 {Black is in no 
hurry to recapture the pawn. It will fall sooner or later.} 6. Nf3 Ne4 {Putting 
pressure on White's pinned piece, and threatening to triple White's pawns on the 
semi-open c-file.} 7. Bd2 Nxd2 {Black grabs the bishop pair.} 8. Nxd2 Bxc5 {Now 
Black can recapture the pawn.} 9. e3 O-O {Black has a very comfortable 
position.} *

